## 6. Loop & Automation Context

This project uses loop engineering with:

- **Global rules**: `loop-rules.md` (the loop constitution — read this first)
- **Agent configuration**: `AGENTS.md` (project-specific verifier setup, stack, commands)
- **Loop definitions**: `LOOP.md` (which loops exist, cadence, step breakdown)
- **State**: `state.md` (per-loop) + `STATE.md` (global triage)
- **Tasks and lessons**: `tasks/todo.md`, `tasks/lessons.md`
- **Run history**: `loop-run-log.md`

Agents must:
- Read `loop-rules.md` on every new session.
- Obey its PLAN → IMPLEMENT → VERIFY order.
- Update `context.md`, `tasks/todo.md`, `state.md` before any code change when goals shift.

